 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">1. What is USB-C PD 3.1 and PPS? (The Technical Edge)</h2>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">USB-C Power Delivery (PD) is a fast charging standard developed by the USB Implementers Forum (USB-IF). The latest iteration, PD 3.1, delivers up to 240W, enough for gaming laptops, workstations, and even desktop equipment. PPS (Programmable Power Supply) enables fine-grained voltage control in 20mV increments, reducing heat generation by up to 30%.</p>

