 <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 border border-slate-200">
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-3">Factory Integration</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Our latest GaN Chargers use PPS (Programmable Power Supply) to dynamically adjust voltage, significantly reducing heat, a critical factor for high-power desktop stations. <a href="https://www.usb.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">USB-IF</a> certification ensures compatibility.</p>
 </div>
 </div>

 <div class="bg-brandOrange/10 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
 <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm"><strong>Why PPS Matters:</strong> Samsung's 45W Super Fast Charging 2.0 <em>requires</em> PPS to work properly. Without this protocol, high-wattage Samsung devices default to standard charging speeds. Every WOWOHCOOL charger with 45W+ output includes PPS support.</p>
 </div>

 <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 border-l-4 border-brandOrange p-5 rounded-r-xl mb-6"><p class="text-[11px] font-black text-brandOrange uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">QUICK ANSWER</p><p class="text-slate-700 text-sm"><strong>What is USB-C PD 3.1?</strong> USB-C Power Delivery 3.1 is the latest fast charging standard supporting up to 240W (Extended Power Range). It enables fast charging for everything from smartphones to gaming laptops through a single USB-C port, with intelligent power negotiation between device and charger for optimal speed and safety.</p></div>

 <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 md:p-6 border border-slate-200 mb-6">
 <h4 class="font-black text-slate-900 uppercase mb-3">The PD Handshake: How a Charger and Device Negotiate Power</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">Every PD-certified charger and device complete a four-step handshake on the CC pin within roughly 50 milliseconds before any high-voltage power flows:</p>
 <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-600 text-sm mb-4">
 <li><strong>Source advertises</strong> all available power profiles (for example 5V/3A, 9V/3A, 15V/3A, 20V/5A, 28V/5A).</li>
 <li><strong>Sink requests</strong> the optimal profile for its current battery state and thermal headroom.</li>
 <li><strong>Source accepts</strong> the request and switches the bus voltage within ~50 ms, then signals PS_RDY.</li>
 <li><strong>Continuous monitoring</strong> renegotiates voltage and current the moment the load changes, for example when a laptop wakes from sleep.</li>
 </ol>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">A "PD-rated" charger that fakes this handshake silently falls back to 5V/3A (15W). USB-IF certified products pass interoperability testing against this exact sequence, which is why genuine certification, not a marketing label, separates a 240W EPR-capable supplier from a counterfeit one.</p>
 </div>

 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">According to USB-IF certification data (USB-IF, 2025), PD 3.1 support in power banks grew 80% year-over-year in 2025. The 140W+ fast charging capability is becoming a key differentiator in the premium segment. This growth trajectory shows no signs of slowing as more devices adopt USB-C as their primary charging port.</p>
 </div>
 </section>

